3. Remix, But Stay Honest.
   You can modify and build upon this work, but don't claim it as your own original creation.
   If you remix it, note what you’ve changed so the history remains clear.

4. Use at Your Own Risk.
   The Software is provided "as is," with no warranty of any kind.
   If it breaks, you get to keep both pieces.

By using this software, you accept these terms with the understanding that code, like poetry, is meant to be shared, remixed, and improved upon—but never exploited.

Now go forth and glam up the code.
